         <abstract>
            <p>Many instructional situations warrant the awarding of letter grades for papers, reports, quizzes, etc. Each of these may constitute a different portion of the final course grade. The process of translating each letter grade to a number, applying the appropriate weighting factor, and then determining the final letter grade, can be bothersome. The author presents a computer program to easily handle this task.</p>
